{{Infobox award | name = IEEE Undergraduate Teaching Award | description = To honor teachers of electrical and electronics engineering and the related disciplines. | reward = The award consists of a bronze medal, certificate, and honorarium. | presenter = [[IEEE]] | country = | year = 1990 | website = [http://www.ieee.org/about/awards/tfas/undergrad.html IEEE Undergraduate Teaching Award] }}
The '''IEEE Undergraduate Teaching Award''' is a [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers#Technical field awards|Technical Field Award]] of the [[IEEE]] that was established by the [[IEEE]] Board of Directors in 1990.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ieee.org/about/awards/tfas/undergrad.html|title=IEEE IEEE Undergraduate Teaching Award|author=|date=|work=Ieee.org|accessdate=14 March 2017}}</ref> It is presented for inspirational teaching of undergraduate students in the fields of interest of the IEEE.
This award may be given to an individual only.
Recipients of this award receive a bronze medal, certificate, and honorarium.
==Recipients== The recipients of the IEEE Undergraduate Teaching Award include the following people:<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20100619222920/http://ieee.org/documents/undergraduate_rl.pdf] </ref> * 2016: Terri Fiez <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/silicon-forest/index.ssf/2015/06/terri_fiez_former_head_of_engi.html|title=Terri Fiez, former head of engineering and computer science at Oregon State, lands a top post at CU Boulder|author=|date=|work=Oregonlive.com|accessdate=14 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/silicon-forest/index.ssf/2013/12/oregon_state_created_crisis_by.html|title=Oregon State mishandled dismissal of Terri Fiez, created 'crisis' in engineering school, tech leaders say|author=|date=|work=Oregonlive.com|accessdate=14 March 2017}}</ref> * 2015: Branislav M. Notaros * 2014: Hsi-Tseng Chou * 2013: Charles Kenneth Alexander <ref>{{cite web|url=http://facultyprofile.csuohio.edu/csufacultyprofile/detail.cfm?FacultyID=C_K_ALEXANDER|title=CSU Faculty Profile Detail - Cleveland State University|author=|date=|work=Csuohio.edu|accessdate=14 March 2017}}</ref> * 2012: Santosh K. Kurinec <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eds.ieee.org/eds-members-named-recipients-of-ieee-technical-field-awards.html|title=EDS Members Named Recipients of IEEE Technical Field Awards {{!}} IEEE Electron Devices Society|website=eds.ieee.org|language=en-gb|access-date=2018-11-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ethw.org/Santosh_K._Kurinec|title=Santosh K. Kurinec - Engineering and Technology History Wiki|author=|date=|work=Ethw.org|accessdate=14 March 2017}}</ref> * 2011: Raghunath Shevgaonkar <ref>{{cite web|url=http://ethw.org/Raghunath_K._Shevgaonkar|title=Raghunath K. Shevgaonkar - Engineering and Technology History Wiki|author=|date=|work=Ethw.org|accessdate=14 March 2017}}</ref> * 2010: Ned Mohan <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ece.umn.edu/facultyECE/ECEFACULTYNEDMOHAN.html|title=Directory – Electrical and Computer Engineering|author=|da