{{Infobox laboratory | name = NASU Institute for Nuclear Research | image = KINR-image 01.jpg | established = 1970 | operating_agency = [[National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine]] | director = Vasyl Ivanovych Slisenko | address = Prospekt Nauky, 47, MSP 03680 [[Kiev]], [[Ukraine]] | website = [http://www.kinr.kiev.ua www.kinr.kiev.ua] |}}
'''Institute for Nuclear Research of the [[National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine]]''' ('''KINR''') ({{lang-ua|Інститут ядерних досліджень Національної академії наук України}}) located in [[Kiev]], [[Ukraine]]. The Institute publishes journal [[Nuclear Physics and Atomic Energy (journal)|Nuclear Physics and Atomic Energy]].
==History== Soon after the [[World War II]], in 1944 at the [[NASU Institute of Physics|Institute of Physics]] in [[Kiev]] was created a department for dealing with number of issues concerning nuclear physics and use [[atomic energy]]. For execution of outlined activities sequentially were placed into operation: in 1956 a [[cyclotron]] U-120, in 1960 a research reactor VVR-M (Water-Water), and in 1964 an electro-static generator EGP-5.
On 26 March 1970 the Presidium of the [[National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine]] (at that time Ukrainian Academy of Sciences) in pursuance of the relevant resolution of the Council of Ministers of the [[Ukrainian SSR]] adopted the resolution #105 about the creation of NASU Institute of Nuclear Research (IYaD) on the basis of a number of nuclear departments of the [[NASU Institute of Physics]].
==Major scientific directions== The main directions of scientific research are [[Nuclear Physics]], [[Atomic Energy]], [[Solid-state physics]], [[Plasma Physics]], [[Radiobiology]] and [[Radioecology]].
==Experimental facilities== Research [[Nuclear reactor]] WWR-M, [[Cyclotron]] U-120, [[Isochronous cyclotron]] U-240, 10 MeV [[Electrostatic nuclear accelerator|Electrostatic Tandem Accelerator]].
==Directors== * 1970 — 1974 [[Mitrofan Pasichnyk]] * 1974 — 1983 [[Oleh Nimets]] * 1984 — 2015 [[Ivan Vyshnevskyi (scientist)|Ivan Vyshnevskyi]] * 2015 — [[Vasyl Slisenko]]
==Known scientists== *[[Aleksandr Leipunskii]] *[[Vilen Strutinsky]] *[[Yuri G. Zdesenko]]
