'''Mzuzu University''' is one of the principal universities of [[Malawi]]. The school is located in [[Mzuzu]], in the northern region of Malawi. It was founded in 1997 and accepted its first students in 1999. At the time the university opened its doors, the Chancellor was Malawi's former president Dr Bakili Muluzi and the first Vice Chancellor was Professor Terrence Davis. Professor [[Peter Mwanza]], who later entered politics and became a cabinet minister, was active in establishing the university. He was Chairman of the University Council, and later Vice Chancellor.<ref name=PressTrust>{{cite web |url = http://www.presstrust.org.mw/profile-professor-peter-n.-mwanza-b.sc.-m.sc.-ph.d.html |title = Profile: PROFESSOR PETER N. MWANZA, B.Sc., M.Sc., Ph.D. |publisher = Press Trust |accessdate = 2011-03-03 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110722222930/http://www.presstrust.org.mw/profile-professor-peter-n.-mwanza-b.sc.-m.sc.-ph.d.html |archivedate = 2011-07-22 |df = }}</ref>
